@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(USE-INIT-FORCE, 0018)
' @cycle(USE-INIT-MIGRATE, 0018)
' @cycle(USE-INIT-RALPH, 0022)
' @id(USE-INIT-FORCE)
' @desc(USE-INIT-FORCE, "Implemented: `mdd init --force` (Commands::Init { force } in crates/mdd-cli/src/main.rs) supplies an always-Overwrite conflict handler to Project::init_with_conflict_handler, so every REGENERABLE scaffolding file — the .mdd/docs/*.md, the workflow SKILL.md files under .claude/skills and .codex/skills, the CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md managed blocks, and the SessionStart hook — is overwritten from the current templates with no per-file prompt. Without --force the command passes prompt_init_conflict, keeping today's per-file [o/S] prompt. The three accumulating STATE files are routed through write_yaml_create_or_migrate, which never consults the handler, so --force cannot overwrite config/trace/approvals. Realized by SEQ-INIT-SCAFFOLD; owned by CMP-INIT-CLI + CMP-INIT-ENGINE.")
' @id(USE-INIT-MIGRATE)
' @desc(USE-INIT-MIGRATE, "Implemented: on every `mdd init` the three state files are written through Project::write_yaml_create_or_migrate (crates/mdd-core/src/lib.rs). When the on-disk `version` is older than the tool's current schema version (StateFile::schema_version, read from each struct's Default) the file is parsed through the current struct so fields added since fill from #[serde(default)], its version is bumped, and it is re-serialized — accumulated links, approvals, and config preserved. Equal version leaves the file byte-for-byte untouched (idempotent); a newer version is never downgraded. A migrated file is reported on a `migrated` line, distinct from `overwrote`. Realized by SEQ-INIT-SCAFFOLD; owned by CMP-INIT-ENGINE.")
' @id(USE-INIT-RALPH)
' @desc(USE-INIT-RALPH, "Implemented: `mdd init` scaffolds the Ralph workspace (crates/mdd-core/src/lib.rs init_with_conflict_handler + crates/mdd-core/src/templates.rs). The mdd-ralph SkillTemplate is part of templates::WORKFLOW_SKILLS, so its SKILL.md is written under .claude/skills and .codex/skills by the same REGENERABLE loop as every other skill (--force overwrites). The dirs list now includes .mdd/ralph. .mdd/ralph/PROMPT.md is written via write_text_if_missing (REGENERABLE, templates::ralph_prompt()). .mdd/ralph/PLAN.md is written via the new write_text_create_if_missing (templates::ralph_plan()) — the SeededOnce path (DOM-INIT-SEED-ONCE): created only when missing, never overwritten (the conflict handler is not consulted, so --force cannot reach it) and never migrated, because the plan is consumed-and-rewritten state any source may own. Realized by SEQ-INIT-SCAFFOLD; owned by CMP-INIT-ENGINE.")
' Current-side use cases for cycle 0018 (--force + migrate) and cycle 0022
' (Ralph workspace), mapped from the implemented init scaffolder.
title MDD init — force-overwrite scaffolding + forward-migrate state (current)

left to right direction

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev

rectangle "mdd init" {
  usecase "Overwrite all regenerable\nscaffolding (--force)\nno per-file prompt" as Force
  usecase "Keep per-file [o/S]\nprompt (no flag)" as Prompt
  usecase "Forward-migrate state files\nconfig / trace / approvals\n(never overwrite)" as Migrate
  usecase "Scaffold the Ralph workspace\nmdd-ralph skill + PROMPT.md (regenerable)\nseed PLAN.md once (never overwrite)" as Ralph
}

Dev --> Force
Dev --> Prompt
Dev --> Migrate
Dev --> Ralph

Force ..> Prompt : <<extend>> (replaces prompt)

note bottom of Force
  USE-INIT-FORCE: --force = always-Overwrite handler
  over the regenerable files. The three state files
  bypass the handler and are migrated, not overwritten.
end note

note bottom of Migrate
  USE-INIT-MIGRATE: write_yaml_create_or_migrate upgrades
  a state file only when on-disk version < current;
  equal = untouched; newer = never downgraded.
end note

note bottom of Ralph
  USE-INIT-RALPH: init seeds the Ralph workspace.
  mdd-ralph SKILL.md + .mdd/ralph/PROMPT.md are
  Regenerable (--force overwrites). .mdd/ralph/PLAN.md
  is SeededOnce: write_text_create_if_missing, never
  overwritten (even by --force) and never migrated.
end note
@enduml
